<div class=3D"sqs-html-content" data-sqsp-text-block-content=3D"">
  <h2 style=3D"text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;">Quick Answers</h2><=
h4 style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;">How long is a cubit in the Bible?</h4><p=
 class=3D"" style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;">A cubit is about <strong>18 inc=
hes</strong> or <strong>45 centimeters</strong>=E2=80=94the length from the=
 elbow to fingertips. Noah=E2=80=99s Ark was 300 cubits long, or roughly <s=
trong>450 feet</strong>.</p><h4 style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;">How much is=
 a shekel worth?</h4><p class=3D"" style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;">A shekel=
 weighed around <strong>11.5 grams (0.4 oz)</strong> of silver. It was roug=
hly equal to a day=E2=80=99s wage in Old Testament times.</p><h4 style=3D"w=
hite-space:pre-wrap;">What is a talent in the Bible?</h4><p class=3D"" styl=
e=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;">A talent was a unit of weight, about <strong>75=
 pounds (34 kg)</strong>. One talent of gold today would be worth over $2 m=
illion.</p><h4 style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;">What is a mite in the Bible?=
</h4><p class=3D"" style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;">A mite (lepton) was the =
smallest coin in circulation=E2=80=94worth <strong>1/128 of a denarius</str=
ong>, or less than a penny today.</p><h4 style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;">Wh=
at is a denarius?</h4><p class=3D"" style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;">A denar=
ius was a Roman silver coin equal to <strong>one day=E2=80=99s wage</strong=
> for a laborer (<a class=3D"bibleref" target=3D"_BLANK" href=3D"https://ww=
w.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=3DMatthew%2020:2&amp;version=3DNRSVA&amp=
;src=3Dtools">Matthew 20:2</a>).</p><h4 style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;">Wha=
t is a mina in the Bible?</h4><p class=3D"" style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;"=
>A mina was a unit of currency equal to <strong>50=E2=80=9360 shekels</stro=
ng>, or about <strong>1.25 pounds (0.6 kg)</strong> of silver.</p><h4 style=
=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;">How tall was Goliath?</h4><p class=3D"" style=3D=
"white-space:pre-wrap;">Goliath stood <strong>6 cubits and a span</strong>=
=E2=80=94around <strong>9 feet 9 inches</strong> tall (<a class=3D"bibleref=
" target=3D"_BLANK" href=3D"https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=3D=
1%20Samuel%2017:4&amp;version=3DNRSVA&amp;src=3Dtools">1 Samuel 17:4</a>).<=
/p><h4 style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;">How big was Noah=E2=80=99s Ark?</h4>=
<p class=3D"" style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;"><a class=3D"bibleref" target=
=3D"_BLANK" href=3D"https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=3DGenesis%=
206:15&amp;version=3DNRSVA&amp;src=3Dtools">Genesis 6:15</a> describes it a=
s <strong>300 cubits long, 50 wide, 30 high</strong>=E2=80=94about <strong>=
450 x 75 x 45 feet</strong>.</p><h4 style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;">What is=
 a bath in the Bible?</h4><p class=3D"" style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;">A b=
ath was a unit of liquid measure, equal to about <strong>6 gallons (22 lite=
rs)</strong>. It was used for temple vessels.</p><h4 style=3D"white-space:p=
re-wrap;">What is an ephah in the Bible?</h4><p class=3D"" style=3D"white-s=
pace:pre-wrap;">An ephah measured <strong>about 5.8 gallons (22 liters)</st=
rong> of dry goods. Gideon offered an ephah of flour in <a class=3D"biblere=
f" target=3D"_BLANK" href=3D"https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=
=3DJudges%206:19&amp;version=3DNRSVA&amp;src=3Dtools">Judges 6:19</a>.</p><=
h4 style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;">What is a Sabbath day=E2=80=99s journey?=
</h4><p class=3D"" style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;">Roughly <strong>2,000 cu=
bits</strong>, or <strong>0.6 miles (1 km)</strong>=E2=80=94the maximum all=
owed distance to walk on the Sabbath (<a class=3D"bibleref" target=3D"_BLAN=
K" href=3D"https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=3DActs%201:12&amp;v=
ersion=3DNRSVA&amp;src=3Dtools">Acts 1:12</a>).</p><h4 style=3D"white-space=
:pre-wrap;">What is a handbreadth?</h4><p class=3D"" style=3D"white-space:p=
re-wrap;">A handbreadth was about <strong>3 inches (7.5 cm)</strong>=E2=80=
=94the width of four fingers (<a class=3D"bibleref" target=3D"_BLANK" href=
=3D"https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=3D1%20Kings%207:26&amp;ver=
sion=3DNRSVA&amp;src=3Dtools">1 Kings 7:26</a>).</p><h4 style=3D"white-spac=
e:pre-wrap;">What is a homer?</h4><p class=3D"" style=3D"white-space:pre-wr=
ap;">A homer was a large dry measure, about <strong>220 liters (6 bushels)<=
/strong>. Ten homers equaled one ephah (<a class=3D"bibleref" target=3D"_BL=
ANK" href=3D"https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=3DEzekiel%2045:11=
&amp;version=3DNRSVA&amp;src=3Dtools">Ezekiel 45:11</a>).</p><p class=3D"" =
data-rte-preserve-empty=3D"true" style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;"></p><p cla=
ss=3D"" data-rte-preserve-empty=3D"true" style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;"></=
p>
